@page "/aboutUs"

<div class="about-us-container container py-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4">About ALPHA Charity Organization</h1>

    <section class="about-section mb-5">
        <h2>Who We Are</h2>
        <div class="typewriter-container">
            <p class="typewriter-text">
                <span class="typewriter-line">Alpha is a dedicated volunteer charity organization committed to building healthier, safer communities by supporting drug use prevention and offering </span>
                <span class="typewriter-line">care to vulnerable populations.</span>
                <span class="typewriter-line">We believe that collective compassion and proactive efforts can bring positive change and hope to those affected by drug-related challenges.</span>
               
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section mb-5">
        <h2>Our Mission and Vision</h2>
        <p>
            Our mission is to educate, advocate, and support individuals and families to live drug-free lives.
            We envision a community where everyone has access to knowledge, resources, and professional help needed to overcome and prevent substance abuse.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section mb-5">
        <h2>What We Do</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Conduct awareness campaigns and educational workshops in schools, communities, and workplaces.</li>
            <li>Provide support services such as counseling and guidance through trained volunteers and professionals.</li>
            <li>Organize training programs tailored to different age groups: youth, parents, educators, and community leaders.</li>
            <li>Facilitate community events and peer support networks to strengthen social bonds and resilience.</li>
            <li>Collaborate with local authorities and organizations to expand our outreach and effectiveness.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section mb-5">
        <h2>Our Team and Roles</h2>
        <p>
            Alpha’s strength lies in its diverse members, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Volunteers:</strong> The heart of our organization, delivering programs and services.</li>
            <li><strong>Consultants:</strong> Experts providing counseling and professional advice.</li>
            <li><strong>Staff and Managers:</strong> Coordinating activities, logistics, and partnerships.</li>
            <li><strong>Supporters and Donors:</strong> Individuals and groups who contribute resources and help sustain our work.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
        <h2>Meaning of “Alpha”</h2>
        <p>
            Our name “Alpha” embodies the values we hold dear:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>A</strong> – Advocating for change and health</li>
            <li><strong>L</strong> – Love and compassion for all</li>
            <li><strong>P</strong> – Providing support and education</li>
            <li><strong>H</strong> – Hope for a better future</li>
            <li><strong>A</strong> – Awakening awareness and action</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            We strive every day to live up to these principles and make a lasting difference in our communities.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>